@node "AMSD" "Aminet Mini Searcher Downloader"

@{b}Aminet Mini Searcher Downloader@{ub}

 AMSD for short.  AMSD is a GUI based searcher/downloader for Aminet using 
 TCP: port and arexx. AMSD also loads Aminet weekly & daily emails allowing you to 
 download via point and click. AMSD also allows you to send selected file
 names to any open AmIRC/channel. New** View RECENT list & Dir INDEX's

@endnode
@node "req" "Requirements"

  @{b}Requirements for AMSD@{ub}

  Muirexx 3.0a  

  TCP: needs to be mountable
  
  Libs:rexxreqtools.library
  Libs:rexxsupport.library
  Libs:rexxtricks.library
  Libs:rexxdossupport.library

  Sort included with docs by Frédéric RODRIGUES
  Muirequest included with docs by Dave Thomas

  AMSD: dir
  
  Aminet_trees               (Dir) -- contains aminet dir trees & AMSD logo
  Aminet                     (Dir) -- used to store Aminet emails
  
  Yam/rexx/SaveRecent.rexx   This needs to be edited and installed in Yam:

  Amirc/rexx/AMSD.amirx      AmIRC rexx file to start AMSD from AmIRC

  AMSD.readme                This file
  AMSD                       GUI
  AMSD.data                  sample config file
  AMSD.info                  icon
  AMSDCmd.rexx               GUI commands script
  AMSD.guide                 guess you have.....

@endnode
@node "install" "Installation"


  @{b}MANUAL INSTALLATION AMSD package@{ub}

  Copy AMSD dir anyplace on your harddrive.

  Edit the AMSD icon and add the path for MUIREXX

  Check for required libs.

  Click icon GUI will open....    

  Mui bubble help is available....

  When the GUI opens you need to configure the program..

@{b}Search Page@{ub}

   Number slider... set default for max number of finds.
   Search Site ...  set this to you favorite site.. 
                    Only 4 support rexx TCP: search

   
@{b}Download Page@{ub} 

   File & Readme - downloads the readme and the file
   Readme Only   - downloads only the readme 
   File Only     - downloads only the file

   Download Site - your best site.... wuslt seems really slow
   Sorted/Unsorted - this is used for RECENT
   
@{b}Download Page@{ub}   

   ReadmeViewer - select the path for your favorite text viewer
   Download Dir  - Where you want downloaded files to go

   Save Config..... when AMSD is opened again
   it will use data you just saved....

   
   Config for YAM:

  Included is a script to move Aminet emails to the Aminet dir in AMSD
  The script needs to be moved to Yam:rexx and added to Yam:config.
  The Script also needs to be edited for the AMSD/Aminet/ dir

  Script Usage: Click aminet recent email and click the script, the email 
                is saved as a text & named with the date, 
                moved to AMSD/Aminet/


  Manual EXPORTING Aminet Emails-  the recent files needs to have the 
                                   extension .amitxt when it is load 
                                   into AMSD..
                     
  If you use SaveRecent.rexx it renames correctly.  


  Config for AmIRC:

  read the AMSD.rexx for full docs...

@endnode
@node "how" "How do I use it??"

 
  
@{b}Search Page@{ub}

  Just enter text to search for.... no quotes needed...hit return
  It will search the selected aminet site for file containing your text.

  Send Selected files to Amirc Screen-do I need to tell you...
                                      Show someone where file is on aminet

 @{b}Download Page@{ub} 
  
  File & Readme, Readme only, File only- what do you wish to download
  Site Cycle gauge- you pick which site is fastest for you.
  Sorted/Unsorted - AMSD downloads the RECENT from Aminet which is listed
                    by days in Unsorted mode, and Sorted by dir in Sorted mode
  GET Recent- Downloads recent file list from selected site
  View Readme - will download and view the readme of the selected file in a 
                file list...
  Load File - lets you load a Aminet email or Aminet dir tree
  Aminet Dirs Cycle Gagdet- Pick which dir you wish to view it sub dirs
  Load Dir - will load the Dir tree of the one in Aminet Dir gagdet.
  Get Index - One you have a Dirtree loaded you can select a dir and 
              Click GET INDEx and it will get the index of the selected
              Dir
  Download - will download selected file(s) 
  Abort - Aborts current download

  @{b}Clean Up Page@{ub}

  Clear Top - will Clear top view
  Clear Bottom- will Clear bottom view
  Clear All - Clear top & bottom view
  Emergency Exit - Use this if AMSD says it working and its not 
                   Use with extreme care..
  Clean Ram - deletes search.txt and recent from Ram:t/
  Texts Viewer - used to viewer readmes.. Any cli useable textviewer 
                 should work... CED,GED,Multiview,TextView tested.
@endnode
@node "bugs" "Known Bugs"

Do not try to run from 'Ram Disk:' or any other Device with two names..

@endnode
